(firstQuint)Dexmedetomidine Sedation in Children With Respiratory Morbidities.

 Electronic medical records of children with at least 3 characteristics of respiratory morbidities were retrospectively reviewed.

 All study patients received dexmedetomidine bolus over 10 min followed by a continuous infusion to achieve a minimum Ramsay Sedation Score of 5.

 Patients were monitored for hemodynamics, total dose of dexmedetomidine received, adverse events experienced and sedation characteristics.

